{"parse":{"title":"John Blair (historian)","pageid":42853062,"revid":825145896,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p class=\"mw-empty-elt\">\n\n</p>\n<table class=\"infobox biography vcard\" style=\"width:22em\"><tbody><tr><th colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;font-size:125%;font-weight:bold\"><span class=\"fn\">John Blair</span><br /><span class=\"honorific-suffix\" style=\"font-size: 77%; font-weight: normal;\"><span class=\"noexcerpt\" style=\"font-size:100%;\"><a href=\"/wiki/Fellow_of_the_Society_of_Antiquaries_of_London\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Fellow of the Society of Antiquaries of London\">FSA</a>&#32;<a href=\"/wiki/Fellow_of_the_British_Academy\" title=\"Fellow of the British Academy\">FBA</a></span></span></th></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Born</th><td>\n<span class=\"nickname\">William John Blair</span><br /><span style=\"display:none\"> (<span class=\"bday\">1955-03-04</span>) </span>4 March 1955<span class=\"noprint ForceAgeToShow\"> (age&#160;63)</span><br /><span class=\"birthplace\"><a href=\"/wiki/Woking\" title=\"Woking\">Woking</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Surrey\" title=\"Surrey\">Surrey</a>, England</span></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Title</th><td class=\"title\">\nProfessor of Medieval History and Archaeology</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\"><span class=\"nowrap\">Spouse(s)</span></th><td>\n<div style=\"position:relative;display:inline-block;line-height:normal;\">Kanerva Blair-Heikkinen&#32;(<abbr title=\"married\">m.</abbr>&#160;2005)</div></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Parent(s)</th><td>\n<a href=\"/wiki/Claude_Blair\" title=\"Claude Blair\">Claude Blair</a></td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n</td></tr><tr><th colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center\">Academic background</th></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Alma mater</th><td>\n<a href=\"/wiki/Brasenose_College,_Oxford\" title=\"Brasenose College, Oxford\">Brasenose College, Oxford</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\"><a href=\"/wiki/Thesis\" title=\"Thesis\">Thesis</a></th><td>\n<i>Landholding, Church and Settlement in Surrey before 1300</i>&#160;<span style=\"font-size:90%;\">(1983)</span></td></tr><tr><th colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center\">Academic work</th></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Discipline</th><td>\n<div class=\"hlist hlist-separated\"><ul><li>History</li><li>archaeology</li></ul></div></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Sub-discipline</th><td>\n<a href=\"/wiki/History_of_Anglo-Saxon_England\" title=\"History of Anglo-Saxon England\">Early medieval English history</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Institutions</th><td>\n<a href=\"/wiki/The_Queen%27s_College,_Oxford\" title=\"The Queen&#39;s College, Oxford\">The Queen's College, Oxford</a></td></tr><tr style=\"display:none\"><td colspan=\"2\">\n</td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p><b>William John Blair</b>, <span class=\"noexcerpt\" style=\"font-size:100%;\"><a href=\"/wiki/Fellow_of_the_Society_of_Antiquaries_of_London\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Fellow of the Society of Antiquaries of London\">FSA</a>,&#32;<a href=\"/wiki/Fellow_of_the_British_Academy\" title=\"Fellow of the British Academy\">FBA</a></span> (born 4 March 1955) is an English historian, <a href=\"/wiki/Archaeologist\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Archaeologist\">archaeologist</a>, and academic,  who specialises in <a href=\"/wiki/Anglo-Saxon_England\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Anglo-Saxon England\">Anglo-Saxon England</a>. He is <a href=\"/wiki/Professor_(highest_academic_rank)\" title=\"Professor (highest academic rank)\">Professor</a> of Medieval History and Archaeology at the <a href=\"/wiki/University_of_Oxford\" title=\"University of Oxford\">University of Oxford</a>, and a Fellow of <a href=\"/wiki/The_Queen%27s_College,_Oxford\" title=\"The Queen&#39;s College, Oxford\">The Queen's College, Oxford</a>. He gave the 2013 <a href=\"/wiki/Ford_Lectures\" title=\"Ford Lectures\">Ford Lectures</a> at the University of Oxford.\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><input type=\"checkbox\" role=\"button\" id=\"toctogglecheckbox\" class=\"toctogglecheckbox\" style=\"display:none\" /><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2><span class=\"toctogglespan\"><label class=\"toctogglelabel\" for=\"toctogglecheckbox\"></label></span></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Early_life_and_education\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Early life and education</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#Academic_career\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Academic career</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#Personal_life\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Personal life</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#Selected_works\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Selected works</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">5</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Early_life_and_education\">Early life and education</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=John_Blair_(historian)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Early life and education\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Blair was born on 4 March 1955 in <a href=\"/wiki/Woking\" title=\"Woking\">Woking</a>, Surrey, England.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Who&#39;s_Who_2016_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Who&#39;s_Who_2016-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> His father was <a href=\"/wiki/Claude_Blair\" title=\"Claude Blair\">Claude Blair</a>, a museum curator and \"one of the foremost authorities on historic European metalwork, especially arms and armour\",<sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> and his mother was Joan Mary Greville Blair (n\u00e9e Drinkwater).<sup id=\"cite_ref-Who&#39;s_Who_2016_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Who&#39;s_Who_2016-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> \n</p><p>Blair was educated at <a href=\"/wiki/St_John%27s_School,_Leatherhead\" title=\"St John&#39;s School, Leatherhead\">St John's School, Leatherhead</a>, an <a href=\"/wiki/Independent_school_(United_Kingdom)\" title=\"Independent school (United Kingdom)\">independent school</a> in <a href=\"/wiki/Leatherhead\" title=\"Leatherhead\">Leatherhead</a>, Surrey.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Who&#39;s_Who_2016_1-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Who&#39;s_Who_2016-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> He then studied at <a href=\"/wiki/Brasenose_College,_Oxford\" title=\"Brasenose College, Oxford\">Brasenose College, Oxford</a>, graduating with a <a href=\"/wiki/First_Class_Honours\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"First Class Honours\">first-class</a> <a href=\"/wiki/Bachelor_of_Arts\" title=\"Bachelor of Arts\">Bachelor of Arts</a> (BA) degree in 1976.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Who&#39;s_Who_2016_1-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Who&#39;s_Who_2016-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> He remained at Brasenose College to undertake <a href=\"/wiki/Postgraduate_research\" title=\"Postgraduate research\">postgraduate research</a> and completed his <a href=\"/wiki/Doctor_of_Philosophy\" title=\"Doctor of Philosophy\">Doctor of Philosophy</a> (DPhil) degree in 1983.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Who&#39;s_Who_2016_1-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Who&#39;s_Who_2016-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-bio_-_Queen&#39;s_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-bio_-_Queen&#39;s-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> His <a href=\"/wiki/Doctoral_thesis\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Doctoral thesis\">doctoral thesis</a> was titled <i>Landholding, Church and Settlement in Surrey before 1300</i>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Academic_career\">Academic career</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=John_Blair_(historian)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: Academic career\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>During his doctoral research, Blair was a <a href=\"/wiki/Junior_Research_Fellow\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Junior Research Fellow\">Junior Research Fellow</a> at <a href=\"/wiki/Brasenose_College,_Oxford\" title=\"Brasenose College, Oxford\">Brasenose College, Oxford</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-bio_-_Queen&#39;s_3-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-bio_-_Queen&#39;s-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> In 1981, he was elected a <a href=\"/wiki/Fellow_(Oxbridge)\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Fellow (Oxbridge)\">Fellow</a> of <a href=\"/wiki/The_Queen%27s_College,_Oxford\" title=\"The Queen&#39;s College, Oxford\">The Queen's College, Oxford</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Who&#39;s_Who_2016_1-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Who&#39;s_Who_2016-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-bio_-_Queen&#39;s_3-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-bio_-_Queen&#39;s-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> Since then, he has been a <a href=\"/wiki/Praelector\" title=\"Praelector\">praelector</a> and <a href=\"/wiki/Tutorial_system\" title=\"Tutorial system\">tutor</a> in history at the college.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Who&#39;s_Who_2016_1-6\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Who&#39;s_Who_2016-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> On 1 October 2006, he was awarded a <a href=\"/wiki/Title_of_Distinction\" title=\"Title of Distinction\">Title of Distinction</a> by the <a href=\"/wiki/University_of_Oxford\" title=\"University of Oxford\">University of Oxford</a> as \"professor of Medieval History and Archaeology\".<sup id=\"cite_ref-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Blair gave the 2013 <a href=\"/wiki/Ford_Lectures\" title=\"Ford Lectures\">Ford Lectures</a> at the University of Oxford.<sup id=\"cite_ref-6\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup> The lecture series was tiled \"Building the Anglo-Saxon Landscape\".<sup id=\"cite_ref-bio_-_faculty_7-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-bio_-_faculty-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>On 5 May 1983, Blair was elected <a href=\"/wiki/Fellow_of_the_Society_of_Antiquaries_of_London\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Fellow of the Society of Antiquaries of London\">Fellow of the Society of Antiquaries of London</a> (FSA).<sup id=\"cite_ref-8\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-8\">&#91;8&#93;</a></sup> He was elected <a href=\"/wiki/Fellow_of_the_British_Academy\" title=\"Fellow of the British Academy\">Fellow of the British Academy</a> (FBA) in 2008.<sup id=\"cite_ref-BritishAcademy_9-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-BritishAcademy-9\">&#91;9&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Personal_life\">Personal life</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=John_Blair_(historian)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: Personal life\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>In 2005, Blair married Kanerva Heikkinen. Together they have two children; one daughter and one son.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Who&#39;s_Who_2016_1-7\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Who&#39;s_Who_2016-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Selected_works\">Selected works</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=John_Blair_(historian)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" title=\"Edit section: Selected works\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><cite class=\"citation book\">Blair, John (1991). <i>Early Medieval Surrey: Landholding, Church and Settlement before 1300</i>. Gloucester: Alan Sutton Publishing. <a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/978-0-86299-780-9\" title=\"Special:BookSources/978-0-86299-780-9\">978-0-86299-780-9</a>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Early+Medieval+Surrey%3A+Landholding%2C+Church+and+Settlement+before+1300&amp;rft.place=Gloucester&amp;rft.pub=Alan+Sutton+Publishing&amp;rft.date=1991&amp;rft.isbn=978-0-86299-780-9&amp;rft.aulast=Blair&amp;rft.aufirst=John&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AJohn+Blair+%28historian%29\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></li>\n<li><cite class=\"citation book\">Blair, John (1994). <i>Anglo-Saxon Oxfordshire</i>. Oxford, Stroud and Dover, NH: Oxfordshire Books and Alan Sutton Publishing. <a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/978-0-7509-0147-5\" title=\"Special:BookSources/978-0-7509-0147-5\">978-0-7509-0147-5</a>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Anglo-Saxon+Oxfordshire&amp;rft.place=Oxford%2C+Stroud+and+Dover%2C+NH&amp;rft.pub=Oxfordshire+Books+and+Alan+Sutton+Publishing&amp;rft.date=1994&amp;rft.isbn=978-0-7509-0147-5&amp;rft.aulast=Blair&amp;rft.aufirst=John&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AJohn+Blair+%28historian%29\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></li>\n<li><cite class=\"citation book\">Blair, John (2000). <i>The Anglo-Saxon Age: a very short introduction</i>. Oxford: Oxford University Press. <a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/978-0-19-285403-2\" title=\"Special:BookSources/978-0-19-285403-2\">978-0-19-285403-2</a>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=The+Anglo-Saxon+Age%3A+a+very+short+introduction&amp;rft.place=Oxford&amp;rft.pub=Oxford+University+Press&amp;rft.date=2000&amp;rft.isbn=978-0-19-285403-2&amp;rft.aulast=Blair&amp;rft.aufirst=John&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AJohn+Blair+%28historian%29\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></li>\n<li><cite class=\"citation book\">Blair, John (2005). <i>The Church in Anglo-Saxon Society</i>. Oxford: Oxford University Press. <a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/978-0-19-822695-6\" title=\"Special:BookSources/978-0-19-822695-6\">978-0-19-822695-6</a>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=The+Church+in+Anglo-Saxon+Society&amp;rft.place=Oxford&amp;rft.pub=Oxford+University+Press&amp;rft.date=2005&amp;rft.isbn=978-0-19-822695-6&amp;rft.aulast=Blair&amp;rft.aufirst=John&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AJohn+Blair+%28historian%29\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></li>\n<li><cite class=\"citation book\">Blair, John, ed. (2007). <i>Waterways and Canal-building in Medieval England</i>. Oxford: Oxford University Press. <a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/978-0-19-921715-1\" title=\"Special:BookSources/978-0-19-921715-1\">978-0-19-921715-1</a>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Waterways+and+Canal-building+in+Medieval+England&amp;rft.place=Oxford&amp;rft.pub=Oxford+University+Press&amp;rft.date=2007&